channel.title: Unpacking Config Freeze
channel.description:
First off, Hello people :D
Okay, I own an Hp Compaq, kind of an older model. [size=14pt]It plays other clients and webclients,[/size] but when it comes to certain servers it just doesn't work.
Some Backround: [b]Microsoft Windows Xp Sp3[/b] [b]JRE 7[/b] (THE MOST UP TO DATE) [b]Hardware stats are not needed (No need.)[/b]
It Gets to this point VVV Then stops. It can sit like this for any amount of time and never, ever, moves. Please help. [IMG]http://i614.photobucket.com/albums/tt227/nickcasto2/freeze_zps91f4cd78.png[/img]

^^ Is probably correct…Make sure your client is running your cache correctly because your source runs the files and you client runs its files and cache…So it has to do with one of your client files (low chance) or your cache (highe chance)

If this is the case, please elaborate.
